<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I am once again worried that we will once again have our damage dealing role reduced with the release of Shadows of Luclin.<P>The information released so far does not sound very promising to me. A 900 point heal for 400 mana is not very good. The loss of the anti-summoning shield is not good.<P>I don't know if I can go on playing  a mage if they continue to reduce them in power or make them even more ambiguous in purpose. <P>The mage is my favorite class, but hearing all these stories of getting stuffed by melees is downright disheartening. Not being able to solo as well post 55 is disheartening as well. <P>If they shaft mages again with this expansion I feel I will lose interest in this game. I don't really enjoy playing any other class as much as I enjoy playing the mage. But I enjoy playing the mage because of my damage dealing ability. I don't like mod rodding or COTHing only.<P>I want to hammer down on things. The higher lvl you get, the less you seem to be able to do this. Less damage for mage equals less fun for me.
</FONT>
