<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A couple comments..<P>For starters, nobody has said anything about decreasing class power with SoL.  In fact, it's been the opposite - all classes getting new skills, spells, abilities which improve each class.  example: Warriors getting a ability allowing them a greater chance to do tripple attacks is not nerfing mages or bards.  example: Mages getting a ability allowing their pet to do 2 or 3x normal damage for a short period of time is not nerfing clerics or druids.  etc, etc.<P>You do realize that we will now get a chance to CRITICAL with spells?  And an ability to increase our chance to crit?  <P>Regarding your dismay at a 900hp 400mana heal, are you out of your mind?  Exactly what have mages been begging for over the past 2 years?  Way high on the list has been an improved pet heal.  If, on the other hand, you were expecting cleric mana ratio, you might as well start digging through your feces expecting to find diamonds and F-16 jet aircraft.  Our current best spell is 200hp/100mana.  <P>So, not much of a better ratio, but geez, it's 900 friggin hp heal compared to our current 200.  This of itself will GREATLY improve the solo possibility of mages in the end-game.<P>Now, if you really desire to solo post-55, then you shouldn't give a damn about how other classes stack up to you, as long as you can find a static_boring_spawn01, and camp it for 100hrs until you quitely ding alone.  <P>One last thing...you said the higher you get, the less damage you seem to do..I assume you are refering to your damage compared to rogues/monks/warriors/rangers.  <P>Yes, you should expect weapon upgrades for these classes...which will directly increase their damage output, directly increasing the gap between our total output v/s theirs.  Look, it's gonna happen, and it's not looking bad just for mages - don't forget about Necro's, palys, sk's, bards, enchanters, shaman, druids and wizards.<P>You must be forgetting that the fun thing to do in the end game is to GROUP and go KILL STUFF.  i.e. not solo.  Would you prefer the warrior in your group to use a PGT in main hand, or a Sceptre of Destruction?  I would go with SoD, because it would make my group better, allowing us to kill faster, getting more exp and more lewt, and reduce the chance of wipe-outs.  I could care less if that SoD warrior was doing 20x the damage my pet is as long as the group is doing good.<P>Now, that warrior would stand just as good a chance at soloing an ancient wurm in Skyfire with the SoD as with the PGT...so the weapon upgrade is not helping the 'warrior', it's helping each and every GROUP the warrior fights in.  Really, who is benefiting from uber weapons?  <P>Have you ever been group leader, and denied taking a epic rogue because he/she makes you look bad....only to instead invite a paly dressed in bronze so your pet dmg looks good?  Or were you glad to have that epic rogue, because your group killed mobs 25% faster, so were able to take on even more spawns?<P>Think of that next time before you moan about melee weapon upgrades. <P>-Anthe of Luclin<BR>Conjurer
</FONT>
