<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A 900 point, 400 mana heal is NOT the upgrade mages were looking for, especially at such a high level.  This might be a good heal if it was 10 levels lower.  Maybe.  And I can see how it might be good to keep a good pet healthy to shorten downtime, in a group setting.<P>Getting a new pet for the same amount of mana is more efficient (more akin to a complete heal then anything else).  I would probably be more willing to just nuke the tar out of the mob and make it die faster, with that 400 mana, or just start chain-summoning pets, than struggle to keep the pet alive with a terribly innefficient heal.<P>Also, you're completely forgetting anyone that plays in a PvP environment.  You say that having a melee class that can cream a pet without breaking a sweat, and doing uber damage, is good.  Well, that's true, it does make your group more efficient and is welcome if its to your benefit, but if you play on a Zek it's downright disheartening.  <P>The main point is that everyone benefits from incremental upgrades in power as they level, some more than others.  The mage simply doesn't keep pace with the other classes.  The wizard is seeing his nuke improve by 1000 points between level 49 and 60.  The mage sees his improve by 214 points!!  214 points in 11 levels?  The improvement in pet power is very marginal from 49 to 60 as well.  So, unless I'm missing something here, VI either believes that wizards were underpowered, that mages were overpowered or possibly both.  <P>A wizard becomes a much better soloer than a mage does past 50, easy.  It's why you see all those druids and wizards in places like Timorous Deep, Cobalt Scar and Burning Wood quad kiting to their hearts content while the mage either begs for a group or, like you mentioned, camps boring_spawn_01 until his brain is numb.  <P>Do I scorn wizards and druids because they retain (and even advance) their ability to excel?  Hardly.  They should enjoy substantial gains in power as they level.  More power to them.  But I certainly do feel a small amount of envy and wish that things were 'like the old days', back pre-50.  <P>I guess it comes down to how you like to play.  My time is important, and I never waste it sitting at a zoneline /ooc'ing for a group, like I see some people do.  If I can't get a group within 10 minutes, I either want to be able to solo or I'll log off and find something more worth my time.<P>I have also begun life anew on a Zek, which to me is far more interesting now.  The power that the melees enjoy isn't a trivial matter of being jealous that our pets get wooped on by melees.  It's a matter of our competition having the tools to dismantle us in a matter of seconds while we wonder if somebody got the license of the truck that just ran us over (ok, exaggeration, but you get the point).<P>There are so many things I enjoy about the mage and it's why I care enough to rant about what I feel should be fixed.  The magician is a blast to play to 50, and a little beyond, in my opinion, but then the fun dries up as we suffer from incredibly long med times, no mana regeneration, very marginal increases in power and the inability to remain self-sufficient.  I can see how someone that doesn't like to solo, that only groups on a blue server, would disagree; but for me, the mage has been newtered for a while, ever since Kunark, and Luclin doesn't seem to be changing things.
</FONT>
