<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A little perspective...<P>1) Yes some of the new skills will give criticals, mana regen and such.<P>2) No, not everyone will have these as they will take many levels of exp to work in and should not be concidered "standard" for every mage.  Also, melees are getting skills as well, so saying that our new skills balances the lack of new spells would still leave an imbalance since what do casters get to balanace for the new skills that melees get?<P>3) Yes it's great to see melees get new toys that increase their abilities to both survive damage and deal damage.<P>4) No, it's not right that when melees get these new toys to upgrade their characters that no corresponding changes occur to maintain the balance for casters.<P><BR>EQ Is an eternal effort to maintain balance.  The key question is "when were we in balance to benchmark against?".  One cound easily argue that pre-kunark we were all balanced and that in kunark melees got ahead of the casters and that in SoV the melees continuted to gain against casters.  The key question is when did verant think we were in balance?  If verant saw Kunark as the proper balance of casters and melee, then there has not been that much change since then.  <P>Frankly, casters get a lot of perks.  Higher survival rates in encounters, gating, many beneficial spells (invis and IVU, lev, etc.) that make our game play a little easier in non-combat aspects.  If melees have a small advantage to their combat in exchange for lacking the many casting perks then I'm ok with that.<P>But it should never be the case that groups turn down mages or wizzys because we cannot keep up from a damage perspective since we have little to offer other than damage.<P>Conversly they cannot simply add uber spells for us that give us the abilities that make us equals to melees in uber gear because spells are largely "standard equipment" for casters while melees may or may not be able to attain their uber equipment.  <P>I think the quested spells are a great way to handle this.  The new spells that are quested out of WW are a great start.  I'd love to see a new mage spell that would make my mage able to better match up damage wise to melees but that takes the equilivent of a warrior tryig to get a uber weapon in order to get the spell.  And make them the same rarity as the uber weapons. <P>Anyways... at the end of the day, it all comes down to "did you enjoy playing?"  If not (and whatever reason you did not is valid even if everyone else does not think so) then either play something else (diferent class or different game) or don't play for a while.  If the answer is yes, then keep on enjoying it.<P>But remember, everyone has a valid opinion.  If someone is frustrated because their level 55 mage is inferior to a 55 warrior, then they have the right to voice that and not be told that their opinion is not valid.  It is valid.  Likewise those who are happy have an equally valid opinion.<P>Remember, the game is what you make of it.
</FONT>
