I don't think we get the shaft too bad. A little better post50 DMG/Mana ratio would be nice, but not imperitave. <P>As far as being considered top dog (or one of top three dogs) in damage dealing, I think alot of the bad feelings that some have and I used to is from reading these forums and seeing only what is on paper. The reality of magician damage and usefulness is great, IMHO.<P>Last night in Kael Arena, I was one of 3 mages. They put is all in same group with 2 wizzies and a druid. On every pull, we decided if the mob was worth the effort to KS from the other 6 groups. The point being that if we so chose, we always did the most damage of any other group. The funny thing was, none of us cared and were just happy to kill many giants, farm some faction and have no deaths in our group. But I can't recall thinking that it sucked that the wizards could throw 10% more damage per second than me or that there were more tanks than casters. I still am happy to see mobs half the people who play EQ will never see.<P>Another interesting thing is how well received I am in groups and how nice people are to me after we get done doing things. They all say things like "I had no idea mages were this good at killing" or "Wow, those pets rock!" YMMV, but the mage thing is still a cool thing (OK, mezzing big trains with my enchanter is fun) that is topped by little else.<P>--------------------<P>Aan<BR>Player of casters<P>"...trying to clot these little ingrates into shape..."
