A couple more rebuttals for Anthe.  In a group with mellee in it, your pet is never<BR>getting hit at all so putting a DS on it<BR>is a complete waste of mana.  The new pet<BR>aggro rules are that if a PC and a Pet are<BR>both in mellee range of a mob, the mob will<BR>always hit the PC over the Pet,  the only<BR>way to have the pet get hit is to not have<BR>any Player in mellee range of the mob.  So<BR>DS-ing your pet in a normal group is foolish.<BR>So scratch that off the pet investment list.<P>Now burnout, with regards to myself, I have<BR>PoG pants so that burnout 3 on my pet is<BR>mana free and costs me nothing.  Handing<BR>summoned daggers to your pet is also a<BR>waste of time unless you are going against<BR>a mob that fears, then the extra 10 MR is<BR>worth it.  In a normal exp grind, you are<BR>wasting mana.  Now in regards to handing<BR>rings/coldstones to your pet,  yes they<BR>help improve your pets AC and are worthwhile<BR>while soloing or in an oddball group where<BR>your pet is the main tank.  But see the above<BR>agro rules that are currently in place and<BR>this is again a complete waste of time and<BR>mana in a group with real tanks as your pet<BR>is never getting hit anyway.<P>The next biggest problem is mages that have<BR>an unhealthy love for their pets.  The guys<BR>who, resummon ten times to get the hardest<BR>hitting pet, then give it rings and daggers<BR>and DS's and get such an emotional attachment<BR>from doing this, that they now feel that <BR>keeping their pet alive is worthwhile.  It<BR>most assuredly is not,  these are the fools<BR>that get Enchanters killed and give the<BR>rest of us a bad name.  If your pet even looks like he is going to cause trouble for<BR>an enchanter, then the first/best and only<BR>thing you should be doing at that time is<BR>hitting your hotkeyed earthen boots to kill<BR>that pet off NOW.  Anything else, and you<BR>are going to get the Enchanter and the<BR>rest of your group killed.  <P>I generally run with other hits off so have<BR>no idea what my pet is hitting for and really<BR>don't even care.  The pet is strictly a DoT<BR>spell and as long as it is behaving and<BR>hitting the correct mob, all is fine,  if it<BR>isn't, boom, the earthen boots are hit and<BR>I resummon another one.  All my pet gets from<BR>me now in a group is the mana free burnout<BR>from my PoG pants.  Enchanters never have<BR>any trouble from me or my pet in a group and<BR>I have no qualms about killing off my pet <BR>at a moments notice because all I have invested in it is 400 mana.  Mages who invest more than that start to get this idea<BR>that their pet is more important to keep<BR>alive then their group enchanter or begin<BR>to think it is a real group mate and not just<BR>a DoT spell.  <P>Mandrayke<BR>55th Mage Innoruuk
