<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I must admit I try to add in synical humor to draw the occasional grin - I enjoy such efforts by others when I stumble upon it reading threads.  If you get offended at my humor, then my point was probably refering to you, so you should feel like an idiot and not laugh.  Twas my intent.<P>Look - I never said I always max out my pet with summoned items and DS - my topic was with regard to how Mages should be able to solo, and how the 900hp heal is suddenly unwanted or not enough for mages.  Regarding soloing, you are a fool if you don't maximize your tools, unless you are farming greenies or have found a blue mob you can easily take out.  If this is the case, you should get rich selling the /loc info.  <P>Anybody who just uses whatever summons they get without caring to check it's level is a fool, bar none (except epic).  Lets see your 48-hitter air pet do it's job against a level 55 caster mob.  Lets see how many AE waves your all-powerful 50-hitting earth pet can take v/s a 60-hitter.  If I have to explain the vast difference in DPS between min-max summons...not to mention just the resist rate on higher pets...or the aggro danger of weak pets...<P>In the vast world of complaining mages, whining for better pets and better spells...we find quite a few here on these boards who don't even utilize the tools given to them.  So, as such, why even bother moaning?  If you had a summons that ranged from a 54-hiter to 154-hitter, would you then check?  What would it take for you to put out a little effort to make sure you aren't ripping off the efforts of your group?<P>Exactly when should a mage be concerned about what they bring to a group?  Is it really okay to not give a sh1t if my pet sucksass or pulling it's weight?  Is it really okay to use freebie spells v/s burnout IV if it's in my spellbook?  Perhaps the freebie 25ds instead of Cadeau?  Along those lines, why even bother with any spells 55-60?  Why, if you aren't going to utilize them in groups?<P>I never said, or suggested keeping one's pet when it's causing trouble.  Please point out such a quote before you label me as such.  In fact, please point out also where I said I give my pet rings, daggers and coldstones each and ever time I summon.  If you manage to read from left-to-right in an up-down fasion after each sentance, you will realize I was refering to the mana cost of 900hp heal for 400mana to the possiblility of 400mana summons, rings, daggers, bo4, ds, etc.  And you will also realize I was refering to soloing.<P>I would imagine some of you are, in fact, extremely pissed off at your pet's performance.  I would be too, if I was using a 48-hitter and old buffs.  <P>BTW exactly what are you saving your precious mana for?  Do you realize how insignificant your Sirroco cast on every other mob is when compared to a properly buffed 58-quadding water pet on a debuffed mob?
